I"±<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conversational-interfaces-render-knowledge-bases-into-agents">Conversational interfaces</a> can take on <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/few-shot-regime-enables-extreme-customization">different attitudes</a>. Conceiving of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/can-cognitive-tasks-be-factored">factored tasks</a> as managed by specialized <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/reinforcement-learning-agents-model-the-world-as-ds-with-rewarded-transitions">agents</a> might make it more <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cognitive-ergonomics-is-like-biocompatibility-for-tools-for-thought">cognitively ergonomic</a>. This resembles a deck of modifier cards, possibly even Tarot cards (e.g. The Philosopher, The Oracle, etc.), each of which possesses a certain useful <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/skill-exchanges-can-work-like-torrents">skill</a>.</p>
